name: Highway_Management_System
description: A microservice-based backend application for efficient highway ticket management, built with Spring Boot and Spring Cloud. It features dynamic service discovery, centralized configuration, intelligent API routing, and comprehensive testing with Postman. Key services include ticket, vehicle, user, and payment management.

name: OrderNow
description: This is a SpringBoot 3 project based on Microservice Architecture for order management system.

name: Realtime-Notification-System
description: A microservices-based real-time notification system built with Node.js, Express, MongoDB, RabbitMQ, and Socket.IO. It handles high-volume message processing and delivers real-time notifications to users. Key features include JWT authentication, role-based access control, Swagger API documentation, and retry mechanisms for failed message processing.

name: DeRowing
description: An API for a rowing management system to match rowers with teams for competitions and training sessions. Uses the microservices architecture for scalability.

name: Starportal-Real-Time-Notification
description: This project is a real-time notification system built using Node.js, Express, MongoDB, RabbitMQ, and Socket.IO. It allows users to register, log in, and receive real-time notifications. The system is designed using a microservices architecture to ensure scalability and reliability.
